posts.body: Would it be possible to synchronize my ancient image-board-folder with zeronet+torbrowser setup, and thus, hopefully, leading to a situation where we're not stuck with one user trying to seed some one ancient image or video that I already have in the archives?

>baww x is ruining y

Imageboard y being ruined or shut down is merely a question of when, not if. It has always been so, and it will be always be so. If you are unable to adapt and overcome, then you are the normie.

>>17a31937-1e9d-4e18-bda8-73e812b17f6c
qq. Suck it up fuckboi. Past is gone and you're not getting it back no matter how much you cry.

>>9ff22568-af8d-49d2-bbcc-66b240bb3766
Oh it's not going to be, you can be sure of that. Like it or not, we are now in a weapons race. A weapons race between those who want free speech, and those to want to suppress such speech.

>>eb730011-c6fd-421b-8207-165fab7edaa8
It would be really fucking cool to have slavaboo french here atleast. I always enjoyed reading his small essays about various subjects.

Ofcourse, there is the issue of binary succession once again, between this place and millchan.

>>8de22ab9-6f59-486a-9bc2-ef36fc62acaf
I'm all for staying here. However, just in case things don't work out here I made a /k/ board over at millchan.

Hope for the best and prepare for the worst.

>If we're here for more than a couple days

Well it's not like we have options do we? Except for millchan which feels even more broken.

>>c615989c-8e6d-406d-9d83-f6aaed0754be
>I don't think it'll be a big deal since Codemonkey doesn't violate any rules, 
But that doesn't mean anything! If some twatter cunt decides Codemonkey gets banned, then he simply gets banned.

>>3be58e72-fe5e-45de-b11c-9a800af69f18
>>31fcbb05-712b-457a-a427-a4396cb2f2a4
It is a simple weapons-race between those who have something to say, and those who want to silence people who speak out. It's probably going to just escalate from now on.
As I feared. Webm-threads are a thing of the past now.

>>af549500-9480-4364-88d8-cb6a99f3546f
>can't they have dedicated shills only spread the propaganda they want and quietly censor all dissent?
How is that any different from normal /pol/ for example? The signal to noise ratio was absurd in 4 and 8/pol/'s. In here, atleast, users themselves can neutralize the most obvious shills, and there won't be moderator enforced, top-down shilling that takes/took place in 4/8chan.

>>f3d17f9e-e4fb-4036-b663-7151641245b1
What an odd timeline we are living in. Data and knowledge is being erased, and is being permanently lost because of politics that are based on feelings. Nor are we allowed to talk openly and honestly about what is happening around us.


When are we getting servers on Mars?
